{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:15.759842+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here is a summary of how to run, build, and preview this **Vite + React + TypeScript + MUI** admin app.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js** (LTS recommended)\n- **Yarn** (the project uses `yarn.lock`)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Getting Started (Local Development)\n\n### Step 1 – Install dependencies\n```bash\nyarn install\n```\n\n### Step 2 – Copy environment file\nThe `Taskfile.yaml` suggests copying the local env file into the project root:\n```bash\ncp envs/.env.local .env\n```\n\nThe local env (`envs/.env.local`) sets:\n- `VITE_PORT=10086` – dev server port\n- `VITE_HOST=local.lantron.ltd`\n- `VITE_BUILD_ENV=development`\n- `VITE_APP_BASE_API=https://mock.local.lantron.ltd`\n\n### Step 3 – Start the dev server\n```bash\nyarn dev\n# or explicitly: cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host\n```\nThis launches the Vite dev server at **http://localhost:10086** (or whatever `VITE_PORT` is set to). Hot module replacement (HMR) is enabled.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Staging / Test Environment\n\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n# runs: cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite\n```\nUses `envs/.env.stg` (loaded by the Vite config based on `process.env.NODE_ENV`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Building for Production\n\n### Production build\n```bash\nyarn build\n# runs: vite build --mode prod\n```\nUses `envs/.env.prod`, outputs to `dist/`.\n\n### Staging build\n```bash\nyarn build:stg\n# runs: cross-env vite build --mode test\n```\n\n### Explicit production build\n```bash\nyarn build:prod\n# runs: cross-env vite build --mode production\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Previewing the Built App Locally\n\nAfter a build (e.g., `yarn build`), serve the `dist` folder locally with:\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n# runs: vite preview --host\n```\n\nThis starts a local static server (default at http://localhost:4173) to verify the production bundle.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Docker Deployment\n\nA `Dockerfile` is provided for containerised deployment:\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM node:lts-alpine as builder\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY . .\nRUN yarn\nRUN yarn build\n\nFROM nginx:alpine\nCOPY --from=builder /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html\nCOPY --from=builder /app/nginx.conf /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf\nEXPOSE 80\nCMD [\"nginx\", \"-g\", \"daemon off;\"]\n```\n\nBuild and run the container:\n```bash\ndocker build -t admin-app .\ndocker run -p 80:80 admin-app\n```\n\nThe included `nginx.conf` configures:\n- Gzip compression\n- SPA fallback via `try_files` to `index.html`\n- An optional `/admin` sub-path alias\n\n---\n\n## 7. Netlify Deployment\n\nA `netlify.toml` is included for quick Netlify deployments with SPA redirects:\n```toml\n[[redirects]]\n  from = \"/*\"\n  to = \"/\"\n  status = 200\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Environment Files Overview\n\n| File             | Mode / Use          | `VITE_BUILD_ENV` | `VITE_PORT` | `VITE_APP_BASE_API`            |\n|------------------|---------------------|------------------|-------------|---------------------------------|\n| `envs/.env.local` | Local development   | `development`    | `10086`     | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` |\n| `envs/.env.stg`   | Staging / test      | `production`     | `10086`     | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd`   |\n| `envs/.env.prod`  | Production          | `production`     | *(empty)*   | `https://mock.lantron.ltd`       |\n\nThe Vite config (`vite.config.ts`) dynamically loads the correct env file based on `process.env.NODE_ENV` using `dotenv`.\n\n---\n\n## Quick Command Cheat Sheet\n\n```bash\nyarn install              # Install dependencies\ncp envs/.env.local .env   # Set up local env (one-time)\n\nyarn dev                  # Start dev server (localhost:10086)\nyarn dev:stg              # Start dev server with staging env\n\nyarn build                # Production build\nyarn build:stg            # Staging/test build\nyarn build:prod           # Explicit production build\n\nyarn serve                # Preview the built app locally\n\ndocker build -t admin-app . && docker run -p 80:80 admin-app   # Docker\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1124, "prompt_tokens": 7335, "total_tokens": 8459, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 34, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6912}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6912, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 423}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "9cc62ee7-af5d-48bb-8e07-2ad9e4a02d56", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e6-613b-7a40-a45d-d2d29bfe8157-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7335, "output_tokens": 1124, "total_tokens": 8459, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6912}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 34}}}}]}}}
